---
import PolicyLayout from '../../layouts/PolicyLayout.astro';
import SubpagesQuickLinks from '../../components/SubpagesQuickLinks.astro';
---

<PolicyLayout
	title="Privacy Policy"
	description="Privacy Policy for the Audius Song of the Day Discord bot."
>
	<SubpagesQuickLinks />
	<h2>Introduction</h2>
	<p>
		Audius Song of the Day ("the Service") is a Discord bot that selects and
		shares a daily featured track from Audius. This Privacy Policy explains
		what information is collected, how it is used, and your rights regarding
		that information.
	</p>

	<h2>Information We Collect</h2>

	<h3>Discord Information</h3>
	<p>When you interact with the Service, we may store:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Discord user IDs</li>
		<li>Discord server IDs</li>
		<li>Discord channel IDs</li>
		<li>Server configuration settings</li>
		<li>
			User preferences, including whether direct-message notifications are
			enabled
		</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Technical Information</h3>
	<p>We may collect:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Error logs</li>
		<li>Diagnostic information</li>
		<li>Basic service usage statistics</li>
	</ul>
	<p>We do not intentionally collect:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Passwords</li>
		<li>Private Discord messages unrelated to bot commands</li>
		<li>Payment information</li>
		<li>Sensitive personal information</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>How Information Is Used</h2>
	<p>Collected information is used solely to:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Deliver daily song announcements</li>
		<li>Send opted-in direct messages</li>
		<li>Maintain server configuration</li>
		<li>Improve reliability and performance</li>
		<li>Prevent abuse of the Service</li>
		<li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Data Sharing</h2>
	<p>
		We do not sell, rent, or trade personal information. Information may be
		shared only with infrastructure providers used to operate the Service,
		where required by law, or when necessary to protect the security and
		integrity of the Service.
	</p>

	<h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
	<p>
		The Service obtains publicly available track information from Audius and
		operates through Discord. Use of those services remains subject to their
		own terms and privacy policies.
	</p>

	<h2>Data Retention</h2>
	<p>
		Server and user configuration data is retained only as long as necessary
		to provide the Service. Data may be removed when the bot is removed from
		a server, a user disables features that require storage, or the
		information is no longer needed for operation.
	</p>
	<p>
		Operational logs may be retained for a limited period for
		troubleshooting, security, and service reliability purposes.
	</p>

	<h2>Your Rights</h2>
	<p>You may request:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Access to information stored about you</li>
		<li>Correction of inaccurate information</li>
		<li>Deletion of information where applicable</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		Requests may be submitted using the contact information provided below.
	</p>

	<h2>Security</h2>
	<p>
		Reasonable technical and organisational measures are used to protect
		stored information. However, no method of electronic storage or
		transmission can be guaranteed to be completely secure.
	</p>

	<h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
	<p>
		This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically. Continued use of the
		Service following changes constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
	</p>

	<h2>Contact</h2>
	<p>
		Questions regarding this Privacy Policy may be directed to{' '}
		<a href="mailto:toby@tobezdev.com">toby@tobezdev.com</a>.
	</p>
</PolicyLayout>
